The vulnerability knowledge describes a scenario where a lack of enforcement on the maximum allowable depth of stacked filesystems can lead to excessive resource consumption and potential privilege escalation. The solution behavior suggests implementing a check to verify the current stacking depth against a predefined maximum limit before allowing a new mount.

